1
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:34,918
=Vanished Name=

2
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,814
=Episode 5=
(Through Thick and Thin)

3
00:01:42,898 --> 00:01:43,499
Xiaoming.

4
00:01:43,538 --> 00:01:44,658
(2004, Qidaohezi)
Come out, Xiaoming.

5
00:01:44,699 --> 00:01:45,779
Xiaoming, come out.

6
00:01:45,779 --> 00:01:46,378
What's wrong?

7
00:01:46,378 --> 00:01:47,699
- It's your brother.
- Where's the medicine?

8
00:01:47,738 --> 00:01:48,258
Medicine.

9
00:01:51,059 --> 00:01:52,538
Why would you move the medicine?

10
00:02:08,739 --> 00:02:09,499
Xiaofei.

11
00:02:09,899 --> 00:02:10,399
Xiaofei.

12
00:02:11,939 --> 00:02:14,019
Take your medicine. Drink the water.

13
00:02:14,059 --> 00:02:16,219
Lower your head. Swallow it.

14
00:02:16,219 --> 00:02:17,258
Swallow it. Alright.

15
00:02:17,339 --> 00:02:17,899
Good boy.

16
00:02:17,899 --> 00:02:18,978
It's alright.

17
00:02:19,179 --> 00:02:19,739
Swallow it.

18
00:02:19,739 --> 00:02:20,339
Alright.

19
00:02:20,339 --> 00:02:20,839
Xiaofei.

20
00:02:20,939 --> 00:02:21,939
Good boy.

21
00:02:22,219 --> 00:02:23,978
I am here.

22
00:02:25,739 --> 00:02:27,299
Why would you move the medicine?

23
00:02:29,179 --> 00:02:29,779
Freaked me out.

24
00:02:29,818 --> 00:02:31,378
Xiaofei found the medicine once

25
00:02:31,378 --> 00:02:33,059
and almost threw them all away.

26
00:02:33,258 --> 00:02:34,899
So now it's my fault for moving it?

27
00:02:35,059 --> 00:02:36,019
Of course, it is.

28
00:02:36,138 --> 00:02:37,098
Why did he get sick?

29
00:02:37,538 --> 00:02:39,138
Hadn't you been lazy, would he be sick?

30
00:02:41,219 --> 00:02:43,459
You know very well
his disease is congenital.

31
00:02:44,258 --> 00:02:46,098
But you insist on blaming me for it.

32
00:02:46,698 --> 00:02:47,619
So can I say

33
00:02:47,619 --> 00:02:48,779
that it's your karma?

34
00:02:51,818 --> 00:02:53,418
My karma?

35
00:02:53,939 --> 00:02:55,459
Here's your karma.

36
00:02:55,899 --> 00:02:57,978
Where do you think
you're going at this hour?

37
00:03:25,538 --> 00:03:26,538
Xiaoming.

38
00:03:36,578 --> 00:03:37,658
Uncle Qian.

39
00:04:16,818 --> 00:04:17,898
(Uncle Qian.)

40
00:04:18,898 --> 00:04:19,898
(Where have you been?)

41
00:04:21,859 --> 00:04:22,659
(I missed you.)

42
00:04:23,458 --> 00:04:25,539
(Sweetie. Is the lollipop sweet?)

43
00:04:27,059 --> 00:04:27,698
It's okay.

44
00:04:29,138 --> 00:04:30,939
You must learn to praise things.

45
00:04:31,338 --> 00:04:32,898
If you praise this lollipop,

46
00:04:33,258 --> 00:04:34,018
it'll be sweet.

47
00:04:37,299 --> 00:04:38,659
My mom never praises me.

48
00:04:41,578 --> 00:04:43,818
Well, you should learn
to praise your mom first.

49
00:04:44,578 --> 00:04:45,619
Once you praise her,

50
00:04:45,698 --> 00:04:47,539
she'll start praising you, too.

51
00:04:49,698 --> 00:04:50,338
Want it?

52
00:04:50,698 --> 00:04:51,198
No.

53
00:04:51,338 --> 00:04:51,898
You have it.

54
00:05:23,378 --> 00:05:24,859
(Everything is my fault.)

55
00:05:32,258 --> 00:05:33,898
(Am I really that terrible?)

56
00:05:46,659 --> 00:05:47,299
Ren Xiaoming.

57
00:05:57,659 --> 00:05:58,619
What are you doing here?

58
00:06:01,138 --> 00:06:02,138
I...

59
00:06:14,499 --> 00:06:15,138
Let's go.

60
00:06:15,338 --> 00:06:16,299
Where are we going?

61
00:06:27,499 --> 00:06:29,304
It's so late.
Why did you come to my place?

62
00:06:30,878 --> 00:06:32,338
The night market just closed.

63
00:06:32,898 --> 00:06:34,264
I came to see if you went to bed.

64
00:06:35,739 --> 00:06:37,619
Any normal person would've gone to bed.

65
00:06:40,138 --> 00:06:42,138
- I just want to tell you...
- Stop coming.

66
00:06:42,778 --> 00:06:44,179
Some neighbors love to gossip.

67
00:06:48,898 --> 00:06:49,898
Then tell me.

68
00:06:50,338 --> 00:06:52,419
What did I do wrong?
You don't talk to me anymore.

69
00:06:54,338 --> 00:06:55,539
You don't talk to me either.

70
00:06:56,739 --> 00:06:58,859
You keep running away, buddy.
How do I talk to you?

71
00:07:01,619 --> 00:07:02,778
What did you just call me?

72
00:07:03,218 --> 00:07:03,979
Buddy.

73
00:07:06,458 --> 00:07:07,698
Homie.

74
00:07:11,539 --> 00:07:14,218
So we're not dating, right?

75
00:07:17,619 --> 00:07:18,859
Are you crazy?

76
00:07:19,939 --> 00:07:21,179
You idiot.

77
00:07:21,499 --> 00:07:22,939
Who wants to date you?

78
00:07:23,338 --> 00:07:25,299
You're not even a girl to me.

79
00:07:28,659 --> 00:07:30,499
Y-You weren't trying to date me?

80
00:07:31,419 --> 00:07:33,499
Then why did you give me that shirt?

81
00:07:35,499 --> 00:07:37,698
The sleeves on your T-shirt were torn.

82
00:07:38,059 --> 00:07:38,979
You never changed it.

83
00:07:39,578 --> 00:07:41,619
We sell clothes. It was nothing.

84
00:07:46,018 --> 00:07:46,518
Then,

85
00:07:46,578 --> 00:07:48,739
why were you so awkward
when you gave me the shirt?

86
00:07:49,099 --> 00:07:49,979
How was I awkward?

87
00:07:51,059 --> 00:07:53,898
Hey. You couldn't even bend.

88
00:07:53,979 --> 00:07:56,218
You shoved it at me and just ran off.

89
00:07:58,318 --> 00:08:00,739
I hurt my back when helping my mom
move stock the day before.

90
00:08:01,378 --> 00:08:03,499
I ran off because Zhang Fang
was waiting for me.

91
00:08:06,898 --> 00:08:08,939
Then why did you give me tea eggs?

92
00:08:10,939 --> 00:08:12,979
My mom cooked a whole pot.
They'd go bad.

93
00:08:13,218 --> 00:08:15,059
Zhang Fang and the others all got one.

94
00:08:17,258 --> 00:08:18,138
Everyone got one?

95
00:08:20,378 --> 00:08:20,979
Why?

96
00:08:21,299 --> 00:08:22,859
Even a tea egg makes you

97
00:08:22,859 --> 00:08:25,539
feel privileged?
How love-starved is that?

98
00:08:25,539 --> 00:08:26,299
Get lost.

99
00:08:26,539 --> 00:08:27,378
I'm not love-starved.

100
00:08:39,738 --> 00:08:41,698
No wonder you've been acting weird,

101
00:08:42,179 --> 00:08:43,659
throwing brooms and changing seats.

102
00:08:43,899 --> 00:08:46,059
It turns out you've cooked up

103
00:08:46,059 --> 00:08:47,899
a whole romantic drama in just two days.

104
00:08:48,379 --> 00:08:50,179
No wonder Ms. Zhou finds you talented.

105
00:08:50,498 --> 00:08:51,939
You're so talented, you genius.

106
00:08:56,818 --> 00:08:58,299
Why didn't you just say so earlier?

107
00:08:58,299 --> 00:08:59,939
You scared me to death.

108
00:09:03,578 --> 00:09:05,019
Buddies are the best,

109
00:09:05,498 --> 00:09:07,738
through thick and thin.

110
00:09:17,458 --> 00:09:18,059
Buddy,

111
00:09:19,539 --> 00:09:20,818
can we talk somewhere else?

112
00:09:21,618 --> 00:09:22,779
I'm freezing to death.

113
00:09:25,299 --> 00:09:25,939
Let's go.

114
00:09:32,466 --> 00:09:37,080
(2023, Qingzhou)

115
00:10:11,539 --> 00:10:13,299
Help.

116
00:10:13,299 --> 00:10:14,338
Anyone there?

117
00:10:15,059 --> 00:10:17,139
Open the door. Is anyone there?

118
00:11:03,818 --> 00:11:04,578
Xiaoming.

119
00:11:07,218 --> 00:11:08,019
Xiaoming.

120
00:11:08,738 --> 00:11:09,539
It's me.

121
00:11:09,779 --> 00:11:10,498
Bai Shu.

122
00:11:18,338 --> 00:11:19,179
Bai Shu.

123
00:11:22,139 --> 00:11:22,899
Help.

124
00:11:30,059 --> 00:11:30,899
Xiaoming.

125
00:11:33,618 --> 00:11:34,259
Xiaoming.

126
00:11:34,259 --> 00:11:34,939
Xiaoming.

127
00:11:35,419 --> 00:11:36,338
Xiaoming.

128
00:11:39,779 --> 00:11:41,419
Call an ambulance.

129
00:11:44,218 --> 00:11:45,218
Xiaoming.

130
00:11:45,218 --> 00:11:45,779
Xiaoming.

131
00:11:46,338 --> 00:11:47,618
Xiaoming.

132
00:12:08,698 --> 00:12:09,259
Mom,

133
00:12:09,858 --> 00:12:12,299
if I died in that elevator,
what would you do?

134
00:12:13,338 --> 00:12:14,098
What could I do?

135
00:12:14,939 --> 00:12:15,939
Should I die with you?

136
00:12:16,578 --> 00:12:18,379
I still have your brother to look after.

137
00:12:18,539 --> 00:12:19,618
So you're saying

138
00:12:19,618 --> 00:12:21,899
that you and Xiaofei
could live just fine?

139
00:12:22,139 --> 00:12:22,858
What do you mean?

140
00:12:23,539 --> 00:12:24,738
Do we have to die with you

141
00:12:24,738 --> 00:12:26,259
to prove we love you?

142
00:12:26,659 --> 00:12:29,179
Will you ever stop complaining
about being mistreated?

143
00:12:29,698 --> 00:12:33,059
I'm not complaining.
I really hope you two will live well.

144
00:12:34,659 --> 00:12:35,858
Stop being so cheesy.

145
00:12:35,899 --> 00:12:36,498
What's up?

146
00:12:36,978 --> 00:12:37,939
The good die young.

147
00:12:38,419 --> 00:12:39,978
Don't you know how mean you are?

148
00:12:47,939 --> 00:12:48,578
Mom.

149
00:12:50,738 --> 00:12:51,818
I paid the fees.

150
00:12:52,539 --> 00:12:54,808
The doctor said she needs
a little more observation.

151
00:12:55,059 --> 00:12:58,059
But if nothing else comes up,
she can be discharged this afternoon.

152
00:12:58,419 --> 00:12:59,338
I'm not your mom.

153
00:13:00,059 --> 00:13:00,858
I'm her mom.

154
00:13:01,818 --> 00:13:03,458
My daughter was out so late.

155
00:13:03,818 --> 00:13:04,899
Where was she?

156
00:13:05,498 --> 00:13:06,498
Was she robbed?

157
00:13:07,299 --> 00:13:08,179
Hit by a car?

158
00:13:09,218 --> 00:13:10,498
Did she fall into a manhole?

159
00:13:10,858 --> 00:13:11,978
And you just told me,

160
00:13:11,978 --> 00:13:13,299
"She went to her bestie"?

161
00:13:13,659 --> 00:13:15,659
Thankfully, I kept calling her.

162
00:13:15,779 --> 00:13:18,179
She's still alive
because I insisted on going back.

163
00:13:21,738 --> 00:13:23,578
Ren Xiaoming has many faults.

164
00:13:24,818 --> 00:13:26,698
She has a bad temper. She's stubborn.

165
00:13:26,978 --> 00:13:27,858
You are her husband.

166
00:13:28,578 --> 00:13:30,539
Your parents are highly educated.

167
00:13:31,738 --> 00:13:33,738
I'm a folk person who speaks bluntly.

168
00:13:35,498 --> 00:13:37,539
If you don't even care
about your wife's safety,

169
00:13:37,539 --> 00:13:38,858
you're not a real man.

170
00:13:39,179 --> 00:13:41,578
The elevator and the surveillance camera
were out of order?

171
00:13:41,858 --> 00:13:43,498
I think it's your conscience

172
00:13:43,779 --> 00:13:44,779
that's out of order.

173
00:13:44,779 --> 00:13:45,498
Mom.

174
00:13:45,779 --> 00:13:46,818
That's enough.

175
00:13:47,698 --> 00:13:48,659
Go home.

176
00:13:49,139 --> 00:13:50,019
No, I won't.

177
00:13:50,698 --> 00:13:51,578
I'm staying with you.

178
00:13:52,539 --> 00:13:54,738
Mom, you've been here the whole night.

179
00:13:54,899 --> 00:13:57,464
That's nothing. In the hospitals,
I will stay all day and night

180
00:13:57,659 --> 00:13:58,978
until the people are gone.

181
00:14:00,899 --> 00:14:02,738
Mom, are you waiting for me to be gone?

182
00:14:04,379 --> 00:14:04,939
Enough.

183
00:14:04,939 --> 00:14:05,539
Mom.

184
00:14:07,179 --> 00:14:08,659
We're in a hospital.

185
00:14:09,019 --> 00:14:10,139
Just relax.

186
00:14:13,179 --> 00:14:14,059
Go home and rest.

187
00:14:14,578 --> 00:14:15,379
Don't be stubborn.

188
00:14:16,139 --> 00:14:17,179
Talk to him properly.

189
00:14:19,858 --> 00:14:20,978
I'll come in the afternoon.

190
00:14:21,259 --> 00:14:21,759
Okay.

191
00:14:26,659 --> 00:14:27,578
Take care.

192
00:14:31,098 --> 00:14:31,818
See you, Mom.

193
00:14:32,698 --> 00:14:34,059
(She may cause trouble sometimes.)

194
00:14:34,299 --> 00:14:36,139
(But in the end,
I have to count on her.)

195
00:14:49,738 --> 00:14:50,498
Xiaoming.

196
00:14:51,259 --> 00:14:52,578
Mom is right.

197
00:14:53,139 --> 00:14:54,379
It was my fault.

198
00:14:54,578 --> 00:14:55,659
I was too careless.

199
00:14:55,899 --> 00:14:57,779
This whole thing has me scared.

200
00:14:59,338 --> 00:15:01,059
- I should have...
- My...

201
00:15:03,338 --> 00:15:03,858
My...

202
00:15:04,179 --> 00:15:04,818
Bag?

203
00:15:05,899 --> 00:15:06,539
It's here.

204
00:15:06,618 --> 00:15:07,818
It won't get lost.

205
00:15:07,818 --> 00:15:08,818
The diary is there?

206
00:15:17,578 --> 00:15:18,659
Mom just told you

207
00:15:19,098 --> 00:15:20,578
to talk properly with me.

208
00:15:21,978 --> 00:15:22,899
Fine.

209
00:15:25,218 --> 00:15:26,618
I'm going ahead with the lawsuit.

210
00:15:28,978 --> 00:15:30,419
And I want an open trial.

211
00:15:34,939 --> 00:15:35,498
Alright.

212
00:15:39,098 --> 00:15:40,098
Take your phone.

213
00:15:41,379 --> 00:15:43,259
Talk to your bestie about the lawsuit.

214
00:15:53,379 --> 00:15:54,498
Don't push me.

215
00:16:10,899 --> 00:16:11,539
Captain Li.

216
00:16:17,818 --> 00:16:18,978
Alright, guys.

217
00:16:19,218 --> 00:16:21,939
Let's gather all the clues
we have on Zhou Yun.

218
00:16:22,059 --> 00:16:23,578
I need to report to the higher-ups.

219
00:16:24,818 --> 00:16:25,379
Captain Li.

220
00:16:25,539 --> 00:16:28,379
I haven't found any leads
on Zhou Yun yet.

221
00:16:29,498 --> 00:16:30,498
What do you mean?

222
00:16:30,779 --> 00:16:32,338
Shun and I went to the school.

223
00:16:32,578 --> 00:16:35,019
Zhou Yun left the school in 2004

224
00:16:35,139 --> 00:16:37,139
and took her personal file with her.

225
00:16:37,498 --> 00:16:38,419
In 2007...

226
00:16:39,799 --> 00:16:40,818
Get some water. Sorry.

227
00:16:41,299 --> 00:16:42,098
Shun, go ahead.

228
00:16:42,419 --> 00:16:42,978
Alright.

229
00:16:43,139 --> 00:16:44,498
The electronic records

230
00:16:44,498 --> 00:16:46,139
became widespread

231
00:16:46,338 --> 00:16:47,978
nationwide in 2007.

232
00:16:48,379 --> 00:16:49,659
The Qidian Middle School

233
00:16:49,738 --> 00:16:51,338
also entered the information

234
00:16:51,498 --> 00:16:53,299
of the teachers and students

235
00:16:53,498 --> 00:16:54,738
into the system in 2007.

236
00:16:54,978 --> 00:16:58,218
So now, we can only
gather information on Zhou Yun

237
00:16:58,379 --> 00:16:59,338
from people's testimony.

238
00:16:59,818 --> 00:17:01,059
There are no paper records.

239
00:17:01,899 --> 00:17:02,738
Her ID number?

240
00:17:03,379 --> 00:17:04,099
- Nothing.
- Nothing.

241
00:17:04,179 --> 00:17:05,179
No ID number?

242
00:17:05,238 --> 00:17:05,738
No.

243
00:17:05,738 --> 00:17:06,538
No way.

244
00:17:07,379 --> 00:17:08,218
Why not?

245
00:17:08,698 --> 00:17:09,659
Zhou Yun

246
00:17:09,939 --> 00:17:12,579
was hiding her personal information
on purpose.

247
00:17:15,058 --> 00:17:16,280
Yue, tell them what we found.

248
00:17:17,218 --> 00:17:17,939
Well...

249
00:17:18,298 --> 00:17:19,379
Shun and I

250
00:17:19,379 --> 00:17:22,058
went to see the retired teacher,
Wang Yulan.

251
00:17:22,939 --> 00:17:25,258
We also asked some...

252
00:17:25,258 --> 00:17:26,698
Enough, let me take over.

253
00:17:27,099 --> 00:17:27,599
So,

254
00:17:27,859 --> 00:17:30,698
we visited several former colleagues

255
00:17:30,698 --> 00:17:32,819
who worked with Zhou Yun.

256
00:17:33,139 --> 00:17:36,619
They all said Zhou Yun was very odd.
She never used a cellphone

257
00:17:36,819 --> 00:17:38,619
(Hid her identity? ID card)
or socialized with anyone.

258
00:17:39,619 --> 00:17:41,379
She poured almost all her energy

259
00:17:41,379 --> 00:17:42,819
into her students.

260
00:17:43,978 --> 00:17:46,498
She must have been an excellent teacher.

261
00:17:46,698 --> 00:17:47,379
That's right.

262
00:17:47,538 --> 00:17:48,939
Guess what's the weirdest?

263
00:17:49,258 --> 00:17:50,058
What is it?

264
00:17:50,498 --> 00:17:52,379
According to these teachers,

265
00:17:52,538 --> 00:17:53,659
over all these years,

266
00:17:53,978 --> 00:17:56,899
she somehow
never left a single photo behind.

267
00:17:59,298 --> 00:18:01,379
(Why did she hide her identity,)

268
00:18:01,538 --> 00:18:02,778
(Photos)
(not even leaving a photo behind?)

269
00:18:03,899 --> 00:18:06,498
(Hid her identity?)
(Was she trying to hide something?)

270
00:18:07,698 --> 00:18:09,778
(We must look into
every possible related aspect)

271
00:18:10,139 --> 00:18:11,579
(and leave no stone unturned.)

272
00:18:14,778 --> 00:18:18,099
Zhou Yun worked at Qidian Middle School
for so many years.

273
00:18:18,419 --> 00:18:21,538
Theoretically,
she couldn't have been traceless.

274
00:18:25,498 --> 00:18:27,939
This lead is crucial to our case.

275
00:18:28,419 --> 00:18:30,419
Keep digging hard.

276
00:18:30,939 --> 00:18:31,738
Get on it.

277
00:18:31,859 --> 00:18:32,538
Got it.

278
00:18:37,978 --> 00:18:39,538
No information?

279
00:18:49,458 --> 00:18:50,379
Model worker.

280
00:18:50,978 --> 00:18:53,339
Working overtime during the holiday?
Not taking a break?

281
00:18:54,339 --> 00:18:55,538
Aren't you also busy?

282
00:18:56,379 --> 00:18:59,298
I thought asking you out
might be awkward,

283
00:18:59,298 --> 00:19:00,179
so I came

284
00:19:00,298 --> 00:19:02,659
to bring you some coffee.

285
00:19:03,538 --> 00:19:04,379
Here?

286
00:19:04,939 --> 00:19:05,698
Are you sure?

287
00:19:07,379 --> 00:19:08,659
I got a little out of line.

288
00:19:08,859 --> 00:19:10,339
Sorry to disturb you, everyone.

289
00:19:11,258 --> 00:19:11,859
How about this?

290
00:19:12,018 --> 00:19:13,139
(In Memoriam)
Come out for some air.

291
00:19:13,218 --> 00:19:14,339
The coffee is getting cold.

292
00:19:14,538 --> 00:19:15,498
I'll wait outside.

293
00:19:25,298 --> 00:19:26,258
Amazing view.

294
00:19:32,579 --> 00:19:33,698
Seeing it every day,

295
00:19:34,139 --> 00:19:36,099
death isn't so mysterious
or serious anymore.

296
00:19:37,139 --> 00:19:38,659
It's just a routine matter

297
00:19:39,139 --> 00:19:40,778
like eating or having coffee.

298
00:19:41,939 --> 00:19:43,339
But for us police,

299
00:19:43,659 --> 00:19:45,099
we can never treat death

300
00:19:45,099 --> 00:19:46,899
as a routine matter.

301
00:19:48,058 --> 00:19:49,339
Once we become numb to it,

302
00:19:49,939 --> 00:19:51,379
we'll forget

303
00:19:51,899 --> 00:19:53,778
the pain it brings to the living

304
00:19:54,218 --> 00:19:55,819
and our responsibilities.

305
00:19:57,379 --> 00:19:58,899
You're not here for work.

306
00:19:59,978 --> 00:20:00,978
How did you know?

307
00:20:02,058 --> 00:20:03,058
According to regulations,

308
00:20:03,579 --> 00:20:07,458
investigations require
two or more officers to be present.

309
00:20:08,819 --> 00:20:11,498
You even study
criminal investigation rules?

310
00:20:11,498 --> 00:20:12,339
Pretty thorough.

311
00:20:12,939 --> 00:20:15,058
My job gives me a lot of free time.

312
00:20:15,498 --> 00:20:16,698
I learn a bit of everything.

313
00:20:21,179 --> 00:20:23,218
By the way, have you ever fired a gun?

314
00:20:24,899 --> 00:20:26,139
What kind of question is that?

315
00:20:26,179 --> 00:20:27,139
"Have I fired a gun?"

316
00:20:27,218 --> 00:20:28,218
That's my profession.

317
00:20:28,218 --> 00:20:29,139
"Have I fired a gun?"

318
00:20:29,298 --> 00:20:30,379
Have you fired a gun?

319
00:20:32,099 --> 00:20:32,698
Yeah, I have.

320
00:20:36,659 --> 00:20:39,179
There's a live-ammo
shooting club nearby.

321
00:20:39,538 --> 00:20:40,939
I sometimes go there.

322
00:20:41,339 --> 00:20:42,179
It's quite relaxing.

323
00:20:43,538 --> 00:20:44,619
Are you bragging to me?

324
00:20:44,899 --> 00:20:45,859
How are your scores?

325
00:20:47,139 --> 00:20:48,058
Average.

326
00:20:48,778 --> 00:20:49,859
9.6 at 100 meters.

327
00:20:51,498 --> 00:20:52,258
Not bad.

328
00:20:52,659 --> 00:20:55,778
That's actually pretty good
for an average person.

329
00:20:56,099 --> 00:20:58,298
But mine is a ten.

330
00:20:58,778 --> 00:21:00,579
I haven't lost to you in my profession.

331
00:21:07,099 --> 00:21:09,498
Can I ask you something?

332
00:21:10,339 --> 00:21:11,298
Go ahead.

333
00:21:13,339 --> 00:21:14,419
Was Zhou Yun

334
00:21:15,659 --> 00:21:17,859
your and Ren Xiaoming's
middle school homeroom teacher?

335
00:21:19,018 --> 00:21:19,659
Yes.

336
00:21:21,218 --> 00:21:22,939
(2004, Qidaohezi)
(She was nice to both of us)

337
00:21:23,139 --> 00:21:24,458
(and often gave us books.)

338
00:21:25,579 --> 00:21:26,179
Ms. Zhou.

339
00:21:26,778 --> 00:21:28,619
Ren Xiaoming, come in.

340
00:21:33,079 --> 00:21:33,579
How was it?

341
00:21:33,579 --> 00:21:34,458
I got this, Ms. Zhou.

342
00:21:37,099 --> 00:21:38,058
Finished the book?

343
00:21:39,698 --> 00:21:40,298
Any thoughts?

344
00:21:44,419 --> 00:21:46,778
I realized that a person's life is long,

345
00:21:47,419 --> 00:21:48,939
filled with many experiences

346
00:21:49,458 --> 00:21:50,659
and many people.

347
00:21:51,778 --> 00:21:54,538
But in the end,
you don't even know how it ends.

348
00:21:55,579 --> 00:21:57,139
That's what I wanted you to read.

349
00:21:57,659 --> 00:22:00,379
Never label or define yourself.

350
00:22:00,778 --> 00:22:03,698
As long as you want it,
life has infinite possibilities.

351
00:22:05,899 --> 00:22:06,698
Understand?

352
00:22:07,458 --> 00:22:08,258
Yeah.

353
00:22:11,819 --> 00:22:12,819
I checked your grades.

354
00:22:13,538 --> 00:22:16,139
(Academic record)
Stable performance in all subjects.

355
00:22:16,819 --> 00:22:19,778
That means you have a solid foundation.

356
00:22:20,778 --> 00:22:23,379
Would you like to give it a try
and aim for Yucai?

357
00:22:25,859 --> 00:22:26,819
Yucai?

358
00:22:28,258 --> 00:22:29,498
The city's top high school.

359
00:22:30,218 --> 00:22:31,619
No, I won't make it.

360
00:22:32,619 --> 00:22:34,718
Sit down. Don't be nervous. Come on.

361
00:22:37,458 --> 00:22:40,018
If you can't, then who can?

362
00:22:40,339 --> 00:22:41,218
Bai Shu.

363
00:22:42,258 --> 00:22:44,218
I knew you'd say her.

364
00:22:45,099 --> 00:22:46,619
But you're also excellent.

365
00:22:47,778 --> 00:22:48,778
No, I'm not.

366
00:22:49,579 --> 00:22:51,498
My mom says I can't do anything

367
00:22:51,659 --> 00:22:52,939
or accomplish anything.

368
00:22:53,538 --> 00:22:55,099
I'll never catch up to Bai Shu.

369
00:22:58,579 --> 00:23:01,258
Don't make her your only benchmark.

370
00:23:01,619 --> 00:23:03,859
See your own strengths.

371
00:23:04,458 --> 00:23:07,139
Everyone has their own shining points.

372
00:23:08,339 --> 00:23:09,538
Be more confident.

373
00:23:09,819 --> 00:23:12,619
That's how you lead a brilliant life.

374
00:23:18,659 --> 00:23:20,018
I have a book for you.

375
00:23:23,058 --> 00:23:25,419
The Voyage of the Beagle.

376
00:23:26,298 --> 00:23:27,859
This book will tell you

377
00:23:28,058 --> 00:23:30,538
how vast the world is
and how far one can travel.

378
00:23:31,419 --> 00:23:33,778
Go out and see the world.

379
00:23:37,010 --> 00:23:38,904
(The Voyage of the Beagle)

380
00:23:39,498 --> 00:23:40,538
Thank you, Ms. Zhou.

381
00:23:46,298 --> 00:23:48,978
(No one ever told me I wasn't so bad.)

382
00:23:50,298 --> 00:23:52,498
(No one said I had shining points.)

383
00:23:53,538 --> 00:23:54,579
(Except for Ms. Zhou.)

384
00:24:10,139 --> 00:24:12,619
(I never saw
how big the outside world was.)

385
00:24:13,498 --> 00:24:15,258
(I only saw how small my world was.)

386
00:24:16,939 --> 00:24:19,498
(In my world, there were
only potatoes at two-fifty per jin,)

387
00:24:19,619 --> 00:24:20,939
(their ordinary counterparts,)

388
00:24:22,258 --> 00:24:24,498
(animals to be butchered,
and their carcasses.)

389
00:24:26,619 --> 00:24:29,659
(In my world, no one would ever leave.)

390
00:24:30,379 --> 00:24:32,139
(Fate repeated itself for generations)

391
00:24:32,939 --> 00:24:36,978
(in a spiral-shaped apartment building,
forming a cycle of life and death.)

392
00:24:39,819 --> 00:24:41,018
(In my world,)

393
00:24:41,179 --> 00:24:42,899
(time is usually divided)

394
00:24:42,899 --> 00:24:45,579
(into time to make money
and time to rest)

395
00:24:45,579 --> 00:24:47,058
(in order to make more money.)

396
00:24:47,778 --> 00:24:49,179
(The vast universe exists)

397
00:24:49,339 --> 00:24:51,778
(to highlight how small my home is,)

398
00:24:53,058 --> 00:24:54,778
(so small it's like a speck of dust.)

399
00:24:57,659 --> 00:24:59,619
(Dust has no nutrients.)

400
00:25:00,698 --> 00:25:02,978
(I'm just inorganic matter
within that dust.)

401
00:25:04,298 --> 00:25:06,218
(Inorganic matter doesn't grow.)

402
00:25:07,498 --> 00:25:10,339
(Aiming for Yucai? What a joke.)

403
00:25:57,234 --> 00:26:06,584
(Qidaohezi Qidian Middle School)

404
00:26:46,659 --> 00:26:47,538
Cheap potatoes.

405
00:26:49,859 --> 00:26:50,738
Cheap potatoes.

406
00:26:53,698 --> 00:26:55,298
Do you know how amazing your world is?

407
00:26:57,538 --> 00:26:58,298
Bai Shu?

408
00:26:58,698 --> 00:27:00,952
Without this, the Mayan civilization
would be incomplete.

409
00:27:03,058 --> 00:27:04,339
This pumpkin is great.

410
00:27:04,819 --> 00:27:08,018
This golden grain
nourished countless civilizations.

411
00:27:08,258 --> 00:27:09,738
Some say it came from outer space.

412
00:27:10,218 --> 00:27:11,458
The corn is great.

413
00:27:12,139 --> 00:27:13,579
You can't just get one.

414
00:27:13,579 --> 00:27:14,339
Take two.

415
00:27:16,339 --> 00:27:17,298
It's even better.

416
00:27:17,498 --> 00:27:19,058
It's a miracle in agricultural history.

417
00:27:19,698 --> 00:27:22,379
Its yield is so high
that other crops can't compete.

418
00:27:23,018 --> 00:27:25,698
Many civilizations survived
because of it.

419
00:27:26,298 --> 00:27:27,058
It's the root.

420
00:27:27,498 --> 00:27:30,099
Take some more and don't starve.

421
00:27:31,619 --> 00:27:33,379
You find them ordinary

422
00:27:33,698 --> 00:27:35,298
because you see them every day

423
00:27:35,458 --> 00:27:35,978
and forget

424
00:27:36,018 --> 00:27:38,218
that they're as great as
those rare plants.

425
00:27:38,859 --> 00:27:40,738
No life on Earth is simple.

426
00:27:41,458 --> 00:27:42,339
Including you and me.

427
00:27:43,179 --> 00:27:44,419
Why didn't you go home?

428
00:27:46,379 --> 00:27:47,419
- Let's go.
- Hey.

429
00:27:47,778 --> 00:27:49,579
You bought nothing after all that talk

430
00:27:49,659 --> 00:27:51,298
about the Mayan civilization?

431
00:27:51,698 --> 00:27:52,778
I just wanted to tell you

432
00:27:53,139 --> 00:27:54,498
that your writing is beautiful.

433
00:27:55,698 --> 00:27:57,298
You should show it to more people.

434
00:27:58,859 --> 00:27:59,579
Let's go to Yucai.

435
00:28:02,018 --> 00:28:03,058
Stop hesitating.

436
00:28:03,698 --> 00:28:05,139
I won't make it.

437
00:28:05,419 --> 00:28:07,139
You haven't tried, so how do you know?

438
00:28:07,538 --> 00:28:08,058
Come on.

439
00:28:08,659 --> 00:28:09,339
Join me.

440
00:28:10,778 --> 00:28:11,278
Forget it.

441
00:28:12,099 --> 00:28:14,218
Come on, let's try together.

442
00:28:15,698 --> 00:28:17,978
Pinky swear, a hundred years,
no take-backs.

443
00:28:18,659 --> 00:28:20,538
It's settled. Seal it.

444
00:28:40,778 --> 00:28:41,899
Where are the slippers?

445
00:28:42,339 --> 00:28:43,458
No need to change.

446
00:28:43,738 --> 00:28:44,579
That won't do.

447
00:28:44,579 --> 00:28:45,579
I came from outside.

448
00:28:46,298 --> 00:28:48,899
We don't have so many rules. Come on in.

449
00:28:50,419 --> 00:28:50,919
Come here.

450
00:28:51,698 --> 00:28:54,899
Let me show you
my super-duper huge bedroom.

451
00:28:58,099 --> 00:28:59,099
My sofa bed.

452
00:29:00,018 --> 00:29:00,778
It's nice.

453
00:29:03,419 --> 00:29:03,939
Have a seat.

454
00:29:10,778 --> 00:29:11,538
A rat.

455
00:29:12,058 --> 00:29:12,619
What's wrong?

456
00:29:12,738 --> 00:29:13,778
There's a rat.

457
00:29:13,899 --> 00:29:14,778
I heard it.

458
00:29:15,778 --> 00:29:16,659
I heard...

459
00:29:17,419 --> 00:29:17,919
I heard...

460
00:29:19,458 --> 00:29:21,498
A rat.

461
00:29:21,859 --> 00:29:23,099
It was squeaking here.

462
00:29:23,458 --> 00:29:24,859
That sound...

463
00:29:25,778 --> 00:29:26,698
Where is it?

464
00:29:28,619 --> 00:29:29,298
A rat.

465
00:29:30,058 --> 00:29:34,458
We do have a big rat in our house.

466
00:29:34,978 --> 00:29:36,458
Don't scare me.

467
00:29:37,498 --> 00:29:41,058
Look how scared you are. You froze.

468
00:29:42,419 --> 00:29:43,498
Let me show you

469
00:29:44,939 --> 00:29:47,379
this universal super rat.

470
00:29:57,859 --> 00:30:00,579
Ren Xiaofei, my little brother.

471
00:30:01,339 --> 00:30:03,619
He hides in the wardrobe
whenever a stranger comes.

472
00:30:06,859 --> 00:30:08,099
Come out now.

473
00:30:09,099 --> 00:30:09,738
Come on.

474
00:30:11,419 --> 00:30:12,458
Come out.

475
00:30:16,659 --> 00:30:18,738
Hello, Bai Shu.

476
00:30:22,738 --> 00:30:24,179
Hello there, Xiaofei.

477
00:30:24,899 --> 00:30:25,859
I'm Bai Shu.

478
00:30:26,738 --> 00:30:27,859
Nice to meet you.

479
00:30:33,379 --> 00:30:35,139
This coil of yours

480
00:30:35,738 --> 00:30:36,738
is wrong, isn't it?

481
00:30:37,498 --> 00:30:38,258
Let me help you.

482
00:30:39,659 --> 00:30:40,298
See?

483
00:30:41,179 --> 00:30:43,538
Bai Shu is going to fix it for you.
Come out now.

484
00:30:47,419 --> 00:30:49,698
Go ahead and play. I'll cook.

485
00:30:49,899 --> 00:30:51,458
Try my cooking later.

486
00:30:53,099 --> 00:30:53,978
Let me help you.

487
00:30:54,218 --> 00:30:55,258
No need.

488
00:30:56,859 --> 00:30:59,139
I finally got off work early.

489
00:31:02,419 --> 00:31:03,139
This is...

490
00:31:04,258 --> 00:31:05,899
This is Bai Shu, my classmate

491
00:31:06,298 --> 00:31:07,258
and my best friend.

492
00:31:07,339 --> 00:31:08,058
And mine.

493
00:31:08,939 --> 00:31:09,978
And yours?

494
00:31:11,679 --> 00:31:12,179
She is my...

495
00:31:12,179 --> 00:31:12,859
Hello, Auntie.

496
00:31:13,659 --> 00:31:14,738
Auntie, you're so pretty.

497
00:31:15,619 --> 00:31:16,538
What did you say?

498
00:31:17,419 --> 00:31:18,698
Auntie, you're so pretty.

499
00:31:23,179 --> 00:31:26,339
Young lady, you're also pretty
and have great taste.

500
00:31:26,778 --> 00:31:28,139
You two are good friends?

501
00:31:28,619 --> 00:31:29,859
All three of you?

502
00:31:30,659 --> 00:31:32,218
Is dinner ready? Let's eat together.

503
00:31:32,419 --> 00:31:33,258
Not yet.

504
00:31:33,298 --> 00:31:35,339
I just got home
and haven't had time to cook.

505
00:31:35,778 --> 00:31:36,859
Auntie, let me help her.

506
00:31:36,939 --> 00:31:37,439
No need.

507
00:31:37,579 --> 00:31:38,079
Sit down.

508
00:31:38,738 --> 00:31:40,859
How can we let our guest cook?

509
00:31:41,339 --> 00:31:43,458
All of you, sit down. I'll cook today.

510
00:31:43,579 --> 00:31:44,419
Really?

511
00:31:44,738 --> 00:31:47,058
Then I'm in for a treat, Auntie.

512
00:31:47,939 --> 00:31:50,579
You're such a sweet talker.

513
00:31:50,859 --> 00:31:52,218
Why are you so sweet?

514
00:31:52,458 --> 00:31:53,859
What have they been feeding you?

515
00:31:56,258 --> 00:31:57,379
Have fun.

516
00:31:57,859 --> 00:31:58,738
Wait for the food.

517
00:31:59,258 --> 00:32:00,139
Okay, Auntie.

518
00:32:03,498 --> 00:32:05,978
Usually, I cook after I come home.

519
00:32:06,179 --> 00:32:07,218
She eats whatever's ready.

520
00:32:07,538 --> 00:32:09,339
The sun is rising from the west.

521
00:32:09,698 --> 00:32:13,778
♪Summer blooms on the branches♪

522
00:32:13,978 --> 00:32:17,899
♪Roses, roses, I love you♪

523
00:32:18,379 --> 00:32:22,258
- ♪Roses, roses, carry deep affection♪
- Look how happy she is.

524
00:32:22,619 --> 00:32:26,579
- ♪Roses, roses, carry deep affection♪
- She's even singing.

525
00:32:26,619 --> 00:32:29,018
Wasn't it just one compliment
about her looks?

526
00:32:31,298 --> 00:32:33,018
- She is pretty.
- ♪Roses, roses♪

527
00:32:33,058 --> 00:32:34,939
- Prettier than you.
- ♪I love you♪

528
00:32:38,859 --> 00:32:40,619
What? I'm telling the truth.

529
00:32:40,619 --> 00:32:44,738
♪Holy light shines upon the earth♪

530
00:32:47,339 --> 00:32:48,738
You two, hold on a second.

531
00:32:49,659 --> 00:32:50,419
Wait.

532
00:32:52,859 --> 00:32:54,419
Bai Shu, you try it first.

533
00:32:54,419 --> 00:32:54,978
Okay, Auntie.

534
00:32:59,939 --> 00:33:01,659
Oh my, Auntie.

535
00:33:02,099 --> 00:33:03,099
It's amazing.

536
00:33:03,498 --> 00:33:04,939
You're pretty and sing sweetly.

537
00:33:05,379 --> 00:33:06,579
Your cooking is also amazing.

538
00:33:08,538 --> 00:33:11,419
Stop laughing. Your gums are showing.

539
00:33:15,978 --> 00:33:17,218
Have more.

540
00:33:17,698 --> 00:33:18,778
Come often.

541
00:33:19,139 --> 00:33:20,298
I will cook for you.

542
00:33:21,419 --> 00:33:23,419
Bai Shu, do you like our home?

543
00:33:24,339 --> 00:33:25,778
I love it.

544
00:33:27,619 --> 00:33:29,619
Come every day if you want.

545
00:33:29,778 --> 00:33:31,419
If you come, I'll be free.

546
00:33:31,778 --> 00:33:33,179
We have tons of chores.

547
00:33:33,619 --> 00:33:36,619
Washing clothes, cooking,
mopping, and cleaning the house.

548
00:33:37,939 --> 00:33:38,859
No problem.

549
00:33:41,018 --> 00:33:41,778
You...

550
00:33:42,018 --> 00:33:43,458
Xiaoming, which one of you is older?

551
00:33:44,939 --> 00:33:46,859
I was born in February, she in June.

552
00:33:46,899 --> 00:33:48,738
You should call me big sister.

553
00:33:49,738 --> 00:33:51,258
You two are also four months apart?

554
00:33:52,298 --> 00:33:52,899
Yeah, why?

555
00:33:53,939 --> 00:33:55,018
Look how smug you are.

556
00:33:55,538 --> 00:33:58,458
All that extra time on Earth,
and you've got nothing to show for it.

557
00:33:59,498 --> 00:34:01,058
Bai Shu, come often.

558
00:34:01,458 --> 00:34:03,538
Come whenever you want.

559
00:34:03,538 --> 00:34:04,939
I also like Bai Shu.

560
00:34:06,939 --> 00:34:08,859
You barely say anything.

561
00:34:08,978 --> 00:34:10,058
So talkative today?

562
00:34:13,259 --> 00:34:13,899
Auntie.

563
00:34:16,259 --> 00:34:18,779
I came to announce something.

564
00:34:26,699 --> 00:34:27,538
What's so serious?

565
00:34:28,578 --> 00:34:31,138
Xiaoming and I have decided
to aim for Yucai High School.

566
00:34:32,939 --> 00:34:34,138
I didn't say that.

567
00:34:34,538 --> 00:34:35,299
I didn't...

568
00:34:35,618 --> 00:34:37,098
I didn't say that.

569
00:34:37,299 --> 00:34:38,859
I know you're too shy to say it.

570
00:34:40,018 --> 00:34:41,458
Why would I be shy?

571
00:34:41,538 --> 00:34:42,458
It's not like that.

572
00:34:42,458 --> 00:34:43,658
What is Yucai?

573
00:34:44,219 --> 00:34:46,859
Yucai High School, the best in La City.

574
00:34:47,339 --> 00:34:48,379
What? La City?

575
00:34:48,859 --> 00:34:51,578
If she gets into Yucai,
she will have to go to La City?

576
00:34:52,018 --> 00:34:53,339
Yeah, if we get in,

577
00:34:53,859 --> 00:34:55,138
we will live in the dorms there.

578
00:34:56,939 --> 00:34:58,538
Sun Jinfu is from La City, though.

579
00:34:58,779 --> 00:34:59,899
Who is Sun Jinfu?

580
00:35:00,259 --> 00:35:00,779
No idea.

581
00:35:02,058 --> 00:35:03,939
Is this high school expensive?

582
00:35:04,018 --> 00:35:05,699
Does it cost a lot of money?

583
00:35:06,018 --> 00:35:08,138
Auntie, once we pass the exam
and get in,

584
00:35:08,299 --> 00:35:10,138
tuition is the same
as regular high school.

585
00:35:10,578 --> 00:35:11,578
Is the exam hard?

586
00:35:12,098 --> 00:35:13,178
It's really hard.

587
00:35:13,379 --> 00:35:14,498
That's good.

588
00:35:18,859 --> 00:35:20,939
You really don't want me
to get in, do you?

589
00:35:21,779 --> 00:35:22,899
If I get in,

590
00:35:22,978 --> 00:35:24,939
no one will take care
of your precious son, huh?

591
00:35:25,339 --> 00:35:26,138
I'm telling you.

592
00:35:26,138 --> 00:35:28,178
I'll only be your maid
for three more months.

593
00:35:28,259 --> 00:35:29,339
Then you're on your own.

594
00:35:29,538 --> 00:35:30,859
Oh, please.

595
00:35:31,098 --> 00:35:33,699
You talk like
you're guaranteed to get in.

596
00:35:34,299 --> 00:35:36,098
Don't be so smug.
Leave yourself a way out.

597
00:35:36,098 --> 00:35:37,419
Get me some rice.

598
00:35:46,859 --> 00:35:47,538
Auntie.

599
00:35:48,419 --> 00:35:49,899
Xiaoming will definitely make it.

600
00:35:50,219 --> 00:35:50,859
Look at her.

601
00:35:51,578 --> 00:35:52,699
So terrified.

602
00:35:53,259 --> 00:35:55,138
If I didn't push her,
would she dare to try?

603
00:35:57,419 --> 00:35:59,018
Reverse psychology.

604
00:36:07,578 --> 00:36:08,098
Xiaofei.

605
00:36:09,538 --> 00:36:10,458
Why are you crying?

606
00:36:10,739 --> 00:36:13,658
Don't listen to your sister.
She won't get in.

607
00:36:14,299 --> 00:36:16,419
If she got in, I would be a dog, okay?

608
00:36:16,799 --> 00:36:18,538
Don't cry, my boy.

609
00:36:19,299 --> 00:36:20,939
What if I do get in?

610
00:36:23,058 --> 00:36:24,178
What do you want?

611
00:36:25,259 --> 00:36:26,419
If I get in,

612
00:36:27,779 --> 00:36:30,219
circle this table three times
and bark like a dog.

613
00:36:30,618 --> 00:36:31,118
I...

614
00:36:35,018 --> 00:36:39,859
Look how scared she is.
I'm awesome, huh?

615
00:36:50,658 --> 00:36:51,339
Thank you.

616
00:36:52,419 --> 00:36:54,299
I know you came to encourage me.

617
00:36:55,018 --> 00:36:57,578
Not entirely.
I've wanted to visit for a long time.

618
00:36:58,219 --> 00:36:59,458
Now you've seen it.

619
00:36:59,899 --> 00:37:01,178
My whole family is crazy.

620
00:37:02,339 --> 00:37:05,098
I really like your home and your mom.

621
00:37:06,098 --> 00:37:08,339
My mom? Please.

622
00:37:08,419 --> 00:37:09,779
I like your mom.

623
00:37:10,178 --> 00:37:12,219
So gentle and so classy.

624
00:37:12,618 --> 00:37:14,779
But you keep giving her attitude.

625
00:37:15,498 --> 00:37:16,618
If I had a mom like yours,

626
00:37:16,618 --> 00:37:18,138
I'd be over the moon.

627
00:37:18,219 --> 00:37:24,699
She's not a good mom.
And you wouldn't want to be me.

628
00:37:27,379 --> 00:37:28,184
See you tomorrow.

629
00:37:29,578 --> 00:37:31,199
Bai Shu...

630
00:37:45,538 --> 00:37:47,859
Did I say something wrong?
That's just the truth.

631
00:38:12,859 --> 00:38:16,498
You're back. Wash your hands and eat.

632
00:38:21,779 --> 00:38:22,379
I'm not hungry.

633
00:38:26,339 --> 00:38:26,859
Not hungry?

634
00:38:32,899 --> 00:38:33,578
It's fine.

635
00:38:36,978 --> 00:38:38,138
Then don't eat.

636
00:38:59,339 --> 00:39:02,138
I waited for you at the school gate
for two hours today.

637
00:39:04,339 --> 00:39:05,498
I stood the whole time.

638
00:39:07,538 --> 00:39:11,098
You know I have varicose veins
and can't stand for long.

639
00:39:14,299 --> 00:39:16,058
Where were you those two hours?

640
00:39:30,458 --> 00:39:31,578
I treat you so well.

641
00:39:33,859 --> 00:39:35,098
I've given you everything.

642
00:39:39,419 --> 00:39:40,098
But you?

643
00:39:44,058 --> 00:39:45,419
I'm like that fish.

644
00:39:48,339 --> 00:39:49,259
In your heart,

645
00:39:50,779 --> 00:39:52,098
these are all garbage,

646
00:39:54,458 --> 00:39:54,978
right?

647
00:39:56,578 --> 00:39:59,419
You don't cherish them. You don't care.

648
00:40:01,658 --> 00:40:04,739
You leave whenever you want
and refuse to eat.

649
00:40:06,538 --> 00:40:07,658
You're hurting someone

650
00:40:08,219 --> 00:40:09,779
who loves you most

651
00:40:11,498 --> 00:40:13,458
and has raised you from childhood.

652
00:40:17,379 --> 00:40:18,739
Aren't you ashamed?

653
00:40:23,779 --> 00:40:25,098
Are you heartless?

654
00:40:30,018 --> 00:40:30,859
Speak.

655
00:40:31,859 --> 00:40:32,978
I told you to speak.

656
00:40:37,899 --> 00:40:39,219
Why don't you talk?

657
00:40:45,538 --> 00:40:46,299
Torturing me?

658
00:40:50,138 --> 00:40:51,339
Torturing me.

659
00:40:57,658 --> 00:40:59,578
I told you to apologize.

660
00:41:05,978 --> 00:41:07,299
I-I'm sorry.

661
00:41:10,458 --> 00:41:13,259
Say "Mom, I'm sorry."

662
00:41:17,859 --> 00:41:18,419
I'm sorry.

663
00:41:20,899 --> 00:41:23,299
"Mom, I'm sorry."

664
00:41:26,899 --> 00:41:27,859
I'm sorry.

665
00:41:30,138 --> 00:41:33,339
I told you to say "Mom, I'm sorry."

666
00:41:44,219 --> 00:41:46,899
Say it!

667
00:41:47,779 --> 00:41:48,279
I'm sorry.

668
00:41:49,379 --> 00:41:50,098
I'm sorry.

669
00:41:51,498 --> 00:41:52,779
Mom, I'm sorry.

670
00:41:56,379 --> 00:41:57,098
I'm sorry.

671
00:42:15,658 --> 00:42:16,339
Okay.

672
00:42:18,098 --> 00:42:19,339
Wash your hands and eat.

673
00:42:53,699 --> 00:42:54,699
Let's eat.

674
00:42:56,219 --> 00:42:57,498
Let's eat.

675
00:43:00,299 --> 00:43:01,178
Let's eat.

676
00:43:05,000 --> 00:43:12,808
=Vanished Name=
